WEBVTT

00:06.120 --> 00:07.760
[narrator] Dear viewers,

00:07.840 --> 00:10.400
unfortunately, it seems your ill fortune

00:08.000 --> 00:18.000
সাইট খুঁজে না পেলে ব্রাউজারে লিখুন:
-=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

00:10.480 --> 00:13.840
will be dragging you to Patparganj
all over again.

00:15.000 --> 00:17.760
All kinds of desperate cases
come to this court.

00:18.640 --> 00:22.160
Five men together cannot just rob someone.

00:22.240 --> 00:24.280
This is a case of vandalism, your honour.

00:24.360 --> 00:26.880
[squawking] Shit face,
shit face, shithead.

00:26.960 --> 00:28.520
These are not swear words,

00:28.600 --> 00:30.240
- they are just insults.
- Shut up.

00:30.320 --> 00:33.400
[narrator] You will be pleased to see
that while nothing much has changed here,

00:33.480 --> 00:35.560
almost everything has.

00:36.920 --> 00:38.720
The monkeys are still monkeying around.

00:38.800 --> 00:40.640
- And so is the monkey chaser.
- [exclaims]

00:40.720 --> 00:44.920
The lawyers here are still fighting more
over clients than for justice.

00:45.000 --> 00:48.280
But there are some Harvard-returned
anomalies wandering around.

00:48.360 --> 00:49.880
- Hi, I'm--
- [Vishwas] Ananya Shroff.

00:49.960 --> 00:51.960
If you have any complaints
regarding the lawyers' block

00:52.040 --> 00:54.400
- or the judges' block, please come to me.
- Okay.

00:54.480 --> 00:55.560
I'm the Donna of this court.

00:56.760 --> 01:00.960
[narrator] The gap between the foyer
and the chamber is still very wide.

01:01.040 --> 01:04.080
But madam is capable of anything because…

01:04.160 --> 01:05.760
[Daleel] Madam does not argue, okay?

01:05.840 --> 01:07.800
Madam is the argument.

01:07.880 --> 01:09.040
[crowd chanting] Tyagi!

01:09.120 --> 01:10.680
[narrator] The players here
are still the same

01:10.760 --> 01:13.960
who use the long arm of the law
to scratch their backs.

01:15.440 --> 01:18.880
But the influence of the law
can also go a long way.

01:18.960 --> 01:20.600
It's flipped the game.

01:21.760 --> 01:25.040
Tyagi, the real kick is justice.

01:28.280 --> 01:31.920
[Tyagi] You think a sinner like me
can become a judge?

01:32.000 --> 01:34.520
[narrator] When the backbenchers
start calling the shots,

01:35.280 --> 01:37.040
things are bound to change.

01:37.120 --> 01:38.120
Stay tuned.

01:40.760 --> 01:42.160
Whether crazy or unbelievable…

01:42.240 --> 01:43.240
BASED ON SOME TRUE EVENTS

01:43.320 --> 01:45.080
…a lot of true incidents
are coming your way.

01:45.160 --> 01:46.160
[vehicle crashes]

01:46.240 --> 01:47.880
BASED ON SOME TRUE ACCIDENTS

01:47.960 --> 01:51.400
[narrator] What?
Accidents? Again? [chuckles]

01:54.080 --> 01:55.880
- [Order] He's here.
- [Mintu] Cool. [clears throat]

01:56.880 --> 01:57.960
[Mintu] All rise.

01:58.040 --> 02:03.600
Making his entry is the Principal
District Judge of Patparganj Court,

02:04.280 --> 02:06.040
ex-Bar President,

02:06.600 --> 02:08.320
and my GOAT…

02:09.000 --> 02:13.520
[both] His honour, VD Tyagi!

02:28.160 --> 02:29.520
[vocalising]

02:30.880 --> 02:32.400
[upbeat music playing]

02:42.360 --> 02:43.480
[music fades]

02:43.560 --> 02:45.080
What the hell am I doing?

02:45.160 --> 02:46.840
[vocalising]

02:47.880 --> 02:49.480
I'm going to be a judge,

02:50.600 --> 02:52.960
and I'm going to dance
like this at my oath ceremony?

02:53.040 --> 02:55.680
[sighs] Bro, you're hardly
going to dance like this.

02:56.320 --> 02:59.720
You'll do a Michael Jackson! [vocalises]

02:59.800 --> 03:02.440
- No, sir. Y-you can do this one.
- Hey, hey.

03:03.000 --> 03:04.560
- Hey!
- Yeah.

03:05.120 --> 03:06.760
Stop the bloody chicken dance, man.

03:10.800 --> 03:13.160
[chuckles] So cool you are looking, bro.

03:15.360 --> 03:16.360
Am I?

03:16.880 --> 03:21.200
But, Tyagi, I'll miss you like hell, bro.

03:21.280 --> 03:23.960
- Hey, come on. [laughs]
- [whimpers]

03:24.720 --> 03:28.160
- I'm going to be a judge at last.
- Yeah. [chuckles]

03:28.240 --> 03:31.520
Tyagi, sir.
It's time for your oath ceremony.

03:32.440 --> 03:34.920
Terrific. So, let's really quickly
rehearse the oath, sir. Shall we?

03:35.000 --> 03:37.600
Hey. He's the Principal District Judge.

03:37.680 --> 03:39.160
Do you know what that means?

03:39.240 --> 03:41.240
[stammers] Means he's a judge, right?

03:41.320 --> 03:43.120
He's the judge above other judges.

03:43.200 --> 03:45.520
- Over and above?
- Yeah.

03:45.600 --> 03:49.400
Not a single sheet of paper will move
in Patparganj Court without his approval.

03:49.480 --> 03:50.800
[gleeful music playing]

03:50.880 --> 03:54.920
Henceforth, the BC and AD eras are over.

03:57.280 --> 04:00.520
And VD Tyagi's era begins.

04:16.360 --> 04:19.280
[Sujata] I thought I'd distribute
my new card to everyone before I leave.

04:19.360 --> 04:22.840
[chuckles] Here, if you have a client
who's out of your league, give it to them.

04:23.800 --> 04:24.800
[chuckles]

04:24.880 --> 04:27.880
If you work hard like me, then one day
you'll have a chamber of your own.

04:28.560 --> 04:29.640
Maybe.

04:29.720 --> 04:32.840
- [crying]
- Daleel. Hey.

04:34.240 --> 04:35.760
He's on some kind of bad trip.

04:36.880 --> 04:38.680
Aw, Daleel, it's okay.

04:39.200 --> 04:40.680
She's just moving to the chamber.

04:40.760 --> 04:42.320
- She'll be in touch with you.
- [chuckles]

04:42.400 --> 04:43.560
No, no, Ani.

04:43.640 --> 04:45.120
A good cry lightens you up.

04:45.200 --> 04:48.000
- Daleel, you keep crying.
- [sobbing]

04:48.080 --> 04:51.360
Wow, wow, wow. Amaz…

04:53.840 --> 04:55.480
Sujata, there's a spelling mistake here.

04:55.560 --> 04:56.960
[bystander] Look at this.

04:57.040 --> 05:01.720
These people don't even know that advocate
is spelled with a double D. [laughs]

05:01.800 --> 05:03.160
- Oh.
- [Ani] Mr. Shukla,

05:03.240 --> 05:05.040
chamber is spelled incorrectly.

05:05.120 --> 05:06.440
Look down.

05:06.520 --> 05:08.200
They've written, "Chembur."

05:08.840 --> 05:12.200
Sujata, chamber is C-H-A-M--

05:12.280 --> 05:14.120
Look, if you know so much,
join me in the chamber.

05:14.200 --> 05:16.120
God knows what kind of partner
Mintu is going to be.

05:16.200 --> 05:19.520
If you're with me, then we two lasses
can kick their asses and everything--

05:19.600 --> 05:20.600
Suja--

05:21.400 --> 05:22.560
Sir, so sorry.

05:23.200 --> 05:26.000
Sujata, I've only just started
getting cases.

05:26.600 --> 05:30.040
Let me win my first case,
get a little more practice.

05:30.120 --> 05:33.840
And then, like you, I'll earn my place
in the chamber, I promise.

05:33.920 --> 05:36.160
Hey, the chief guest has arrived!

05:36.240 --> 05:39.600
Vishwas has called all of you
for the oath ceremony.

05:39.680 --> 05:42.600
Our own Mr. Tyagi's being sworn in.
Come on.

05:42.680 --> 05:47.320
…and that I will uphold
the constitution of India and the laws.

05:47.400 --> 05:52.560
And that I will uphold
the constitution of India and the laws.

05:56.080 --> 05:58.080
- And this court--
- Hey, careful.

05:58.720 --> 06:00.800
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations. Thank you.

06:00.880 --> 06:04.160
This court offers a hearty welcome
to the new Additional District Judge,

06:04.240 --> 06:05.760
Mr. Kailash Shubhkela.

06:06.720 --> 06:09.280
And now, it is my distinct pleasure
and honour

06:09.360 --> 06:13.360
to invite our Principal District Judge,
Mr. Visheshwar Dayal Tyagi,

06:13.440 --> 06:16.200
to the podium to come and take the oath.
Sir.

06:26.880 --> 06:28.880
- [judge] I…
- [clears throat]

06:31.120 --> 06:33.400
I, Visheshwar Dayal Tyagi…

06:33.480 --> 06:36.600
[judge] …will perform
the duties of my office

06:36.680 --> 06:41.280
without fear or favour,
affection or ill will,

06:41.360 --> 06:46.200
and that I will uphold
the constitution of India and the laws.

06:46.280 --> 06:52.120
…perform the duties of my office
with… [coughs] …fear or favour,

06:52.200 --> 06:57.560
affection or ill will, and that
I will uphold the constitution of India…

06:57.640 --> 07:00.800
- Hey, did he say with or without? Huh?
- …and the laws.

07:09.680 --> 07:11.320
Was it with or without?

07:19.080 --> 07:20.400
[theme music plays]

07:31.240 --> 07:32.360
[music ends]

07:32.440 --> 07:34.160
[siren blaring]

07:35.680 --> 07:38.160
[groans] My friends.

07:39.920 --> 07:41.880
He could barely handle one.

07:43.000 --> 07:45.280
When her sexy twin sister walked in,

07:46.320 --> 07:48.000
wearing even skimpier clothes.

07:49.480 --> 07:51.680
Suddenly, they smell the fragrance.

07:51.760 --> 07:53.680
[sniffs, moans]

07:54.320 --> 07:56.320
They see a guy standing there.

07:56.400 --> 07:58.200
Fairly dashing, just like me.

07:58.800 --> 08:01.040
Both of them lose their senses

08:01.560 --> 08:04.080
and pounce on him, drooling and moaning.

08:04.760 --> 08:06.720
Then they tear off his clothes.

08:07.920 --> 08:09.240
And then?

08:09.320 --> 08:11.040
Then the ad comes to an end.

08:11.120 --> 08:12.560
Oh.

08:14.480 --> 08:15.640
What was the name you said?

08:15.720 --> 08:18.040
Fire Clone Deodorant.

08:18.120 --> 08:20.560
Spray more, play more.

08:21.600 --> 08:25.320
His armpits are like a lotus in a swamp,
they're burnt.

08:25.400 --> 08:27.960
- [sniffs] But what a fragrance.
- [patient chuckles]

08:29.000 --> 08:31.840
For three years, I've been spraying more
every single day.

08:31.920 --> 08:34.320
- But are you playing more?
- What nonsense.

08:34.400 --> 08:37.640
If Mr. Banaspati says yes,
will you apply it as well?

08:37.720 --> 08:39.200
[patients] Yes. Yeah.

08:39.280 --> 08:40.280
[patient] Why not?

08:43.000 --> 08:47.720
Sir, this is exactly why
we must have this product discontinued.

08:47.800 --> 08:50.320
So that we can safeguard our people

08:51.320 --> 08:52.840
from getting badly burnt.

08:54.480 --> 08:57.680
Gentlemen, this ad is a lie.

08:59.720 --> 09:01.720
Girls don't get impressed by all this.

09:02.520 --> 09:06.400
What girls really like is personality,
confidence.

09:06.960 --> 09:07.960
Just be yourself.

09:08.040 --> 09:11.760
[chuckles] I tried doing that too.

09:11.840 --> 09:13.400
She filed a police report.

09:13.480 --> 09:14.960
[patients chuckling]

09:15.880 --> 09:18.560
Now, when I finally get
the compensation money,

09:18.640 --> 09:20.880
I'm going to use it to buy me a bride.

09:20.960 --> 09:22.680
- [patient 1] Good idea.
- [patient 2 laughs]

09:22.760 --> 09:25.480
- [chuckles]
- My God, Mr. Banaspati.

09:26.560 --> 09:28.080
You're so sexist.

09:28.160 --> 09:29.720
[chuckles]

09:30.600 --> 09:32.240
Madam, you know,

09:32.320 --> 09:35.120
I didn't even think of myself as sexy.

09:35.920 --> 09:40.520
You skipped sexier
and you jumped straight to sexiest.

09:40.600 --> 09:42.440
[patients laugh]

09:42.520 --> 09:46.120
Madam, we'll have to run some tests to
find out the exact cause of these burns.

09:46.800 --> 09:48.760
If the tests turn out to be in our favour,

09:48.840 --> 09:51.080
will you come to the consumer court
and testify?

09:51.720 --> 09:53.160
Yeah, please, do come.

09:53.240 --> 09:56.560
The people from the company
have been threatening me.

09:56.640 --> 09:59.880
They said they've got this lawyer
who studied abroad.

09:59.960 --> 10:01.680
She's a hotshot lawyer.

10:02.200 --> 10:05.440
Her name… [stammers]
…sounded a lot like the number nine.

10:05.520 --> 10:07.120
Wait, Nayana?

10:07.200 --> 10:09.040
Y-yes, Nine-a.

10:09.120 --> 10:11.040
Do not say Arora.

10:11.120 --> 10:12.960
Okay, I won't say it.

10:13.040 --> 10:14.400
[scoffs]

10:14.480 --> 10:16.960
But it is her. [chuckles]

10:19.440 --> 10:21.960
[assistant] The High Court has sent
iPhones for all of you.

10:22.040 --> 10:23.360
Sir, which one would you like?

10:23.440 --> 10:27.400
Midnight black or starlight white?

10:28.240 --> 10:29.600
I protest.

10:31.880 --> 10:33.360
Same here.

10:33.440 --> 10:35.440
Look, you didn't even give us
the option of rose gold.

10:35.520 --> 10:36.920
What?

10:37.000 --> 10:38.960
I mean, the High Court judges have them.

10:39.040 --> 10:40.040
They have them, right?

10:40.120 --> 10:41.720
- The rose gold ones.
- Yes, sir.

10:41.800 --> 10:43.360
You're not being very fair to me.

10:44.360 --> 10:47.280
I protest this shameless opulence.

10:48.440 --> 10:49.480
[chuckles]

10:49.560 --> 10:52.840
How does this make
the judiciary of Patparganj look?

10:52.920 --> 10:58.000
If an impoverished person walks in
seeking redress and justice from you,

10:58.960 --> 11:02.240
and he sees you carrying
a rose gold iPhone,

11:03.160 --> 11:04.400
what will he think?

11:05.040 --> 11:07.360
How intimidated is he going to feel?

11:08.440 --> 11:11.680
Sir, yesterday in court
there was this poor guy.

11:11.760 --> 11:13.080
Even he had an iPhone.

11:13.160 --> 11:14.200
So?

11:14.280 --> 11:15.680
Pro Max.

11:16.360 --> 11:18.600
Sir, I was the one
who was feeling intimidated.

11:18.680 --> 11:19.920
- [workers laughing]
- I mean…

11:20.000 --> 11:21.120
[clears throat]

11:21.720 --> 11:25.600
I will file an official written complaint

11:25.680 --> 11:28.720
to the Principal District Judge
of this court…

11:31.040 --> 11:32.760
once we have one.

11:33.320 --> 11:36.360
- We do have Tyagi.
- [workers mumbling]

11:46.400 --> 11:48.560
Your honour, congratulations.

11:48.640 --> 11:50.680
- [chuckles]
- It's such a thrill to see you here.

11:50.760 --> 11:51.760
- Thank you.
- [chuckles]

11:52.320 --> 11:53.680
- Sir, this is Peepal.
- Sir.

11:53.760 --> 11:55.640
- He's here from the High Court.
- Congratulations.

11:55.720 --> 11:56.720
Thank you.

11:57.680 --> 12:00.280
This is Rajkumar Rana.
He is your security head.

12:00.880 --> 12:01.880
Thank you.

12:01.960 --> 12:04.560
And this is Maya Tamang.
Your stenographer.

12:04.640 --> 12:06.920
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

12:09.200 --> 12:10.360
And this is Vipin Topo.

12:10.440 --> 12:11.520
He'll be your code reader.

12:12.080 --> 12:16.080
And assistant, chef, nurse,
travel agent, masseuse…

12:16.160 --> 12:17.160
[coughs]

12:18.320 --> 12:20.520
Judges are the backbone
of the system, your honour.

12:20.600 --> 12:22.480
But they have no one
to take care of their backbone.

12:22.560 --> 12:24.240
- Oh.
- Right.

12:25.440 --> 12:26.440
- I…
- Tyagi, sir.

12:37.000 --> 12:38.000
Tyagi, sir.

12:38.680 --> 12:41.520
Your very first signing
from the High Court. [chuckles]

12:41.600 --> 12:43.520
Along with a special gift
for you, your honour.

12:44.160 --> 12:45.880
Your honour, my number
is first on speed dial,

12:45.960 --> 12:46.960
second is my girlfriend's,

12:47.040 --> 12:48.280
third is my wife's.

12:48.800 --> 12:50.240
You're welcome to call me at any time.

12:50.320 --> 12:52.160
I don't take holidays, I don't fall sick,

12:52.240 --> 12:55.120
my tyre doesn't get punctured,
and my alarm goes off on time.

12:55.200 --> 12:56.200
Sir.

12:56.280 --> 12:57.560
[footsteps approaching]

12:57.640 --> 12:58.880
[Sunil panting] Tya-- Tyagi!

13:01.360 --> 13:03.240
I-- I walked 1200 steps.

13:03.320 --> 13:05.840
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

13:05.920 --> 13:07.400
Listen, Tyagi.

13:08.640 --> 13:12.640
As head of the Vigilance Committee,
I wanted to inform you that

13:13.760 --> 13:15.440
you haven't become a judge yet.

13:16.880 --> 13:18.240
He's just taken the oath.

13:19.720 --> 13:22.760
You took the oath incorrectly.

13:22.840 --> 13:24.160
[ominous music playing]

13:38.120 --> 13:39.320
Oath incorrectly?

13:40.080 --> 13:41.280
[Munshi] Now with Visheshwar gone…

13:41.360 --> 13:42.360
JAGDISH GUPTA

13:42.440 --> 13:44.240
…the responsibility of this chamber
lies with us.

13:44.320 --> 13:45.320
[Order] Yes, Mr. Munshi.

13:45.400 --> 13:47.360
This isn't just Sujata's first day today.

13:48.240 --> 13:51.920
This is also the first day
of a new partnership.

13:52.000 --> 13:54.440
And partnership means equality.

13:55.520 --> 13:59.880
And equality shouldn't just be in words,
but in actions.

13:59.960 --> 14:01.960
Mr. Munshi, what are you so worried about?

14:02.040 --> 14:04.200
Tyagi's left me a huge responsibility.

14:04.280 --> 14:06.040
And I'm gonna create
a great environment here.

14:06.120 --> 14:08.720
\- We are gonna have fun! [chuckles]
- Where do I put all this stuff?

14:08.800 --> 14:09.800
\SUJATA NEGI

14:09.880 --> 14:11.440
\Hey, Ms Sujata. Let me help you.

14:11.520 --> 14:13.960
- I'll take those files. [grunts]
- No, no, it's okay. [grunts]

14:20.760 --> 14:22.720
[clears throat, chuckles]

14:23.640 --> 14:25.680
[romantic music playing]

14:32.200 --> 14:33.200
- [chuckles]
- [Vishwas] Ani!

14:33.280 --> 14:34.680
Ani, I got a cooldrink for you.

14:34.760 --> 14:36.200
I couldn't get one without sugar.

14:36.280 --> 14:38.520
You're definitely winning this case.
Good luck to you.

14:38.600 --> 14:40.040
- [tense music playing]
- Huh?

14:41.920 --> 14:43.040
Are you guys twins?

14:43.120 --> 14:45.640
- So this drink is for her, is it?
- Yeah.

14:46.160 --> 14:49.480
I specifically asked for decaf cappuccino
and lactose-free milk.

14:49.560 --> 14:51.040
Milk minus the milk?

14:51.120 --> 14:52.560
Coffee minus the coffee?

14:53.800 --> 14:55.480
And this black water? [chuckles]

14:55.560 --> 14:57.640
You sure you're not Ani's sister,
by any chance?

14:57.720 --> 14:59.400
- [Ani] Of course not.
- Huh?

14:59.480 --> 15:00.760
Hey. [chuckles]

15:01.320 --> 15:03.960
None of my sisters
would be this grotesque.

15:04.040 --> 15:05.440
Outside and inside.

15:05.520 --> 15:08.160
- Uh, this is--
- Ananya Showoff.

15:08.000 --> 15:18.000
Downloaded from -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

15:08.240 --> 15:10.360
- [stammers]
- Nayana Rora.

15:10.440 --> 15:12.320
Arora. You missed the A.

15:12.400 --> 15:14.520
Just like your last semester at Harvard.

15:14.600 --> 15:16.240
- [sucks teeth]
- [Banaspati] Hey, madam.

15:16.320 --> 15:17.480
This is her.

15:17.560 --> 15:19.880
- She's the Fire Clone lawyer.
- Ooh.

15:19.960 --> 15:22.240
She offered me 100 grand to drop the case.

15:22.320 --> 15:24.080
- Hmm.
- Take it, Mr Banaspati.

15:24.680 --> 15:25.680
It's charity.

15:26.320 --> 15:29.720
And anyway, your lawyer hasn't won
a single case till date.

15:29.800 --> 15:31.120
She's a courtroom virgin.

15:31.200 --> 15:32.680
A virgin?

15:32.760 --> 15:34.560
No. Uh, not that kind.

15:34.640 --> 15:36.760
Thank you so much
for coming today, Nayana.

15:37.320 --> 15:40.880
My first win will be truly special.

15:40.960 --> 15:44.440
Yeah, you'll need all the luck. [chuckles]

15:46.960 --> 15:47.960
[grunts]

15:48.040 --> 15:49.400
Your drink.

15:50.080 --> 15:51.160
[scoffs]

15:54.040 --> 15:55.560
[Vishwas] Ani. Ani, calm down.

15:56.360 --> 15:57.840
Where did you meet her anyway?

15:58.360 --> 15:59.640
Kindergarten.

15:59.720 --> 16:01.080
- Oh.
- [scoffs]

16:01.160 --> 16:03.280
…duties of my office

16:03.360 --> 16:08.240
with… [coughs] …fear or favour,
affection or ill will.

16:10.600 --> 16:11.960
Such a powerful speaker.

16:12.040 --> 16:13.040
[Tyagi] Yeah, right.

16:13.120 --> 16:16.800
Behind the cough, you can clearly hear
the word "out" crystal clear.

16:20.240 --> 16:21.480
What? You guys didn't hear it?

16:21.560 --> 16:23.360
- [stammers]
- Uh, uh, yeah. [stammers]

16:23.440 --> 16:26.440
- Yes, yes. We heard it. [chuckles]
- We-We… We could hear it. Clearly.

16:26.520 --> 16:28.240
But Tyagi, see,

16:29.080 --> 16:33.200
the thing is
Mr Ghosh is a very senior judge.

16:33.800 --> 16:37.360
And what he believes is
you might have said

16:37.440 --> 16:40.000
"with fear or favour" instead.

16:41.080 --> 16:43.720
If there had been no cough,
what would you have heard?

16:45.120 --> 16:47.520
The law doesn't just consider action
but intention,

16:47.600 --> 16:50.480
and you all know that very well.

16:50.560 --> 16:54.680
Tyagi, what I'm trying to say is
that even if you said it wrong,

16:54.760 --> 16:56.160
you still said it right.

16:56.920 --> 17:00.880
I mean, government officers
always work with fear, right?

17:00.960 --> 17:03.560
- Yes. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

17:03.640 --> 17:04.920
- Take us, for instance.
- Hmm?

17:05.000 --> 17:07.480
The press, our peers, superiors
were always a worry.

17:07.560 --> 17:09.760
And now we have live streaming
on top of everything.

17:09.840 --> 17:12.560
And the one who judges without fear
isn't a judge.

17:13.160 --> 17:14.640
- It's the public.
- [chuckles]

17:14.720 --> 17:17.360
Yes, but we can't admit this publicly,
can we?

17:17.440 --> 17:18.600
[chuckling]

17:18.680 --> 17:22.800
Uh, Tyagi, the three of us believe
that you should quickly retake your oath.

17:23.800 --> 17:26.280
Look, even Obama had to do it.

17:26.360 --> 17:27.680
[judge] Which court was that?

17:28.440 --> 17:29.760
Not this one.

17:30.560 --> 17:33.160
- Mr Bhandari, relax. Drink your coffee.
- [both chuckle]

17:33.240 --> 17:35.840
I will not take the oath again.

17:36.920 --> 17:38.400
What's the public going to think?

17:38.480 --> 17:41.200
It's the court's PDJ
can't even take his oath correctly,

17:41.280 --> 17:42.920
how can he take any decisions?

17:43.000 --> 17:45.320
Please give me my stamp back.
I want my stamp back right now.

17:45.400 --> 17:47.120
Tyagi, I do understand,

17:47.200 --> 17:49.560
but my hands are tied, you see.

17:54.240 --> 17:55.280
I understand.

17:56.040 --> 17:57.040
I get it now.

17:59.600 --> 18:01.400
Save your filthy mind for your arguments.

18:01.480 --> 18:03.240
The two of us are just partners, okay?

18:03.320 --> 18:05.760
Sir, even your name
suggests more than a partnership.

18:05.840 --> 18:07.640
Balli, Sujata. A love like no other.

18:10.120 --> 18:12.200
Look, I know you're innocent
in all of this.

18:12.280 --> 18:15.320
But what if
she deliberately bumped into you? Hmm?

18:16.000 --> 18:17.400
You're the bar president.

18:17.480 --> 18:18.680
She only just joined.

18:19.200 --> 18:21.600
She saw how dashing you are.
That's why she hit on you.

18:22.120 --> 18:23.400
- Mmm.
- Yeah.

18:23.480 --> 18:27.040
- I'm gonna hit you instead. Simple idiot!
- Sorry, sorry, sorry. Please don't hit me.

18:27.120 --> 18:28.360
- [shouts]
- Whoa!

18:29.320 --> 18:31.480
[romantic music playing]

18:38.080 --> 18:39.880
S-Sorry, Ms Sujata.

18:41.600 --> 18:44.400
[Vishwas] You know, I've dropped
a lot of files in my time too.

18:44.480 --> 18:46.760
Not to pick them up,
but to create a moment.

18:47.640 --> 18:49.280
But what moment would Mintu want with me?

18:49.360 --> 18:50.920
- Why wouldn't he?
- He's my partner.

18:51.000 --> 18:52.120
- [chuckles]
- [Banaspati chuckles]

18:52.200 --> 18:54.520
Is he your partner,
or does he want to be your partner?

18:54.600 --> 18:55.760
Yeah.

18:56.320 --> 18:59.120
Sujata, I've won the case
before it's even begun.

18:59.200 --> 19:02.040
The doctor has just confirmed
that the burns were caused

19:02.120 --> 19:03.680
- by the chemicals in the deo.
- Hmm?

19:03.760 --> 19:05.280
[Ani] He's willing to testify in court.

19:05.360 --> 19:07.040
Wonderful. Wow.

19:07.120 --> 19:08.240
Well done, Ani.

19:09.000 --> 19:11.200
I'll arrange for you to meet Ahmad
in the Consumer Court.

19:11.280 --> 19:12.320
- Mmm.
- Your case is strong,

19:12.400 --> 19:14.040
- but add some strategy.
- [chuckles]

19:14.120 --> 19:16.800
Sujata, this case
is beyond Nayana's league.

19:17.360 --> 19:21.200
She's an entitled, pampered, bratty bimbo.

19:21.280 --> 19:23.800
She even went to Harvard
because of her father's money.

19:24.400 --> 19:26.080
[bell toll plays]

19:27.840 --> 19:30.000
[stammers] Without the 30% scholarship.

19:30.080 --> 19:32.320
- [Vishwas] Oh.
- Guys, relax. I've got this.

19:33.640 --> 19:37.240
\Tyagi, I can't do anything.
You'll have to handle this on your own.

19:38.040 --> 19:41.160
Why didn't you tell me
that Ghosh was the complainant?

19:41.240 --> 19:43.680
Ma'am, you're afraid of Mr Ghosh?

19:43.760 --> 19:45.040
You should be afraid too.

19:45.120 --> 19:47.920
Judge-itis is what he suffers from.
Judge-itis.

19:48.000 --> 19:50.920
A judge should be like this.
A judge should be like that.

19:51.000 --> 19:53.160
He should do this. She should do that.

19:53.240 --> 19:56.640
Why, just last month,
he complained against a High Court judge,

19:56.720 --> 20:00.000
asking, "Why is he standing on the street
and eating junk food?"

20:00.080 --> 20:02.440
Junk food? How is that a problem?

20:02.520 --> 20:06.120
Publicly,
you cannot open your mouth so wide.

20:06.200 --> 20:07.240
[chuckles]

20:07.320 --> 20:09.880
It's inappropriate for the judiciary.

20:09.960 --> 20:11.640
- This man's the limit.
- Look.

20:11.720 --> 20:14.840
With great difficulty,
I got Ghosh off my back.

20:14.920 --> 20:16.920
I can't help you where he's concerned.

20:17.000 --> 20:18.000
Sorry.

20:20.000 --> 20:21.120
Ma'am.

20:24.200 --> 20:26.080
My dad came for the oath ceremony.

20:26.680 --> 20:29.120
Now, how can I invite him
a second time around?

20:29.640 --> 20:30.920
Just think about it.

20:33.480 --> 20:34.480
Hmm.

20:35.280 --> 20:36.440
I get it, Tyagi.

20:37.480 --> 20:39.120
That you can't take the oath again.

20:40.520 --> 20:42.720
But this court is yours.

20:44.240 --> 20:46.520
So the order should be issued by you.

20:47.120 --> 20:48.560
[upbeat music playing]

20:48.640 --> 20:49.640
Okay?

20:52.000 --> 20:53.920
NORTH

20:54.000 --> 20:55.000
[coughs]

20:55.080 --> 20:56.960
- [Banaspati] Sir?
- [clear throat] Mmm.

20:57.040 --> 20:58.800
First, take off your glasses.

20:58.880 --> 21:00.000
You're in a courtroom.

21:00.600 --> 21:04.240
[groaning] My armpits.

21:08.000 --> 21:11.440
[sexy music playing]

21:14.360 --> 21:16.960
Ma'am, do me a favour.
Put the glasses back on.

21:22.960 --> 21:24.080
Yes. Please proceed.

21:24.160 --> 21:25.240
Look, sir.

21:25.320 --> 21:29.000
Neither am I a movie star,
nor am I some kind of millionaire.

21:29.080 --> 21:32.280
But whenever I spray
some deo on my armpits,

21:32.800 --> 21:35.720
I feel like a million bucks.

21:35.800 --> 21:38.040
I feel like I'm sexist.

21:38.120 --> 21:39.680
[crowd laughing]

21:41.400 --> 21:42.800
Please.

21:43.880 --> 21:44.880
[laughing stops]

21:44.960 --> 21:45.960
Your Honour,

21:46.560 --> 21:51.440
these crony corporates sell their
dangerous products to Banaspati and others

21:51.520 --> 21:54.840
by attacking their insecurities
just to make a profit.

21:54.920 --> 21:56.880
Your Honour, "caveat emptor,"

21:56.960 --> 21:59.040
Latin for "buyer, be aware,"

21:59.120 --> 22:01.600
is one of the foundations
of the Consumer Protection Act.

22:01.680 --> 22:04.080
If someone drinks a soda
and jumps off a roof,

22:04.160 --> 22:06.960
it's not the fault of the advertisement
but the consumer.

22:07.040 --> 22:08.080
Your Honour,

22:08.160 --> 22:11.960
according to this logic, alcohol
and cigarettes should also be advertised.

22:12.040 --> 22:13.360
And why stop there?

22:13.440 --> 22:15.040
Why not sell drugs to children?

22:15.120 --> 22:17.400
- [phone game beeping]
- [crowd laughs]

22:17.480 --> 22:18.960
Uh, um, madam, let's move on.

22:19.040 --> 22:20.960
Um, please present your medical expert.

22:21.040 --> 22:22.200
Absolutely, Your Honour.

22:22.280 --> 22:23.600
Objection, Your Honour.

22:23.680 --> 22:25.440
We have doubts
on the integrity of the expert.

22:25.520 --> 22:30.280
Your Honour, Dr Rizwan is a bonafide
professional with upstanding integrity.

22:30.360 --> 22:31.400
Uh, proceed.

22:31.480 --> 22:34.000
Thank you, Your Honour. Dr Rizwan?

22:34.080 --> 22:35.280
Leave your glasses on.

22:39.480 --> 22:42.760
So, Dr Rizwan, what do your findings say?

22:42.840 --> 22:46.640
The test confirmed the fact
that Mr Banaspati's under arms are burnt.

22:47.240 --> 22:50.560
Correct. And the primary cause?

22:50.640 --> 22:51.960
Oversensitive skin.

22:52.040 --> 22:53.520
[bell toll plays]

22:55.120 --> 22:56.320
What?

22:56.400 --> 22:58.120
Oversensitive skin.

22:59.240 --> 23:03.120
Your Honour,
Mr Banaspati's arms are so delicate

23:03.200 --> 23:07.120
that, not just Fire Clone, any other deo
would also have the same effect.

23:07.200 --> 23:08.240
- Mmm.
- [Ani] Dr Rizwan,

23:08.320 --> 23:09.360
- you're not--
- Your Honour,

23:09.440 --> 23:12.320
- she's intimidating the witness.
- Who has now turned hostile, Your Honour.

23:12.400 --> 23:18.240
Uh-uh. Dr Rizwan is a bonafide
professional with upstanding integrity.

23:20.480 --> 23:22.920
Madam, this testimony will be admitted.

23:23.000 --> 23:26.480
You're welcome to present
another medical expert if you like.

23:27.000 --> 23:28.720
Uh, adjourned.

23:30.400 --> 23:33.400
[dubious music playing]

23:44.960 --> 23:48.600
- Hey, listen, uh, Mr Tendulkar.
- Mmm.

23:48.680 --> 23:53.880
If I want to change Siri's voice
to a female's, what do I do?

23:53.960 --> 23:55.720
Let it be, Sunil.

23:55.800 --> 23:58.320
You'll be asking all kinds of questions.

23:58.400 --> 24:01.560
And if it's a female voice,
it'll make you uncomfortable.

24:01.640 --> 24:05.160
- [chuckles]
- Hmm. [chuckles]

24:07.560 --> 24:08.560
[knocks on door]

24:09.760 --> 24:11.720
Yeah, come in. Come in. Tyagi, come in.

24:12.240 --> 24:14.920
So, this committee hereby proposes

24:15.000 --> 24:17.920
that first thing tomorrow,
you'll take the oath

24:18.000 --> 24:20.800
- and correct your mistake--
- Objection, Mr Sunil.

24:20.880 --> 24:25.120
A complaint was filed before
your committee, saying I made a mistake.

24:26.240 --> 24:28.000
But the mistake hasn't been proven.

24:28.600 --> 24:29.720
Will you come sit down?

24:29.800 --> 24:32.040
[playful music playing]

24:34.360 --> 24:37.160
I said "without fear or favour" that day.

24:38.080 --> 24:40.720
And as per the rules of the committee,

24:40.800 --> 24:44.640
I do have the right
to challenge this complaint.

24:46.760 --> 24:48.600
[sighs] Mr Tyagi.

24:49.200 --> 24:52.160
This committee sits every alternate week.

24:53.320 --> 24:55.560
It'll take us two and a half months
to resolve this.

24:55.640 --> 24:57.080
Two and a half months?

24:57.680 --> 24:58.680
That's too much.

24:59.320 --> 25:00.320
All right.

25:00.960 --> 25:03.440
Till then,
there'll be no PDJ in this court.

25:04.520 --> 25:05.760
Can't help it.

25:07.080 --> 25:09.000
Yes, there'll be some minor issues,

25:09.520 --> 25:11.680
like, uh, leave approval,

25:12.320 --> 25:13.760
vacation benches,

25:13.840 --> 25:15.440
ACR submissions…

25:16.040 --> 25:19.400
But I promise you, I won't let anyone
face any problems at all.

25:20.280 --> 25:22.920
Whether anyone heard it or not,

25:23.880 --> 25:29.920
I've taken an oath that Patparganj Court
will always run as smoothly as possible.

25:31.800 --> 25:32.800
All right.

25:33.640 --> 25:37.560
Tyagi, if this is your final decision,
then… okay.

25:38.160 --> 25:41.160
But there's a tiny problem, Sunil.

25:41.240 --> 25:42.240
What?

25:43.000 --> 25:44.480
- Peepal.
- Yes, sir.

25:45.520 --> 25:47.920
You're the High Court
system officer, right?

25:48.000 --> 25:50.720
Your Honour,
I came here to distribute phones.

25:50.800 --> 25:52.080
I am done with that,

25:52.160 --> 25:55.560
but I haven't received
the official receipt yet from the PDJ.

25:56.120 --> 25:58.160
And you won't receive it either, Peepal.

25:58.240 --> 26:01.320
What can I say? It won't be possible
for two or three months at least.

26:01.400 --> 26:02.400
No way.

26:03.560 --> 26:06.280
In that case, the phones will stay
in the High Court for that time.

26:07.200 --> 26:09.480
- Huh?
- Without the PDJ's stamp,

26:09.560 --> 26:11.160
we can't approve the distribution.

26:12.800 --> 26:14.720
[stammers, groans]

26:14.800 --> 26:15.880
Very sad.

26:15.960 --> 26:17.920
Can't be helped. Our hands are tied.

26:18.000 --> 26:20.200
[triumphant music playing]

27:16.320 --> 27:17.840
Hello, Mr Tyagi.

27:19.280 --> 27:21.080
I must admit I was wrong.

27:22.440 --> 27:26.880
Here, I was thinking that you had said
"with fear or favour" by mistake.

27:27.640 --> 27:32.680
But now, it looks like
that was always your intention.

27:33.680 --> 27:37.000
You are a wonderful addition
to the judiciary.

27:39.560 --> 27:44.080
I hope your father's legacy
is in safe hands.

27:44.680 --> 27:46.960
He would be proud of you.

27:47.040 --> 27:49.240
[sombre music playing]

28:17.200 --> 28:18.760
[Mintu] It's gonna be fun.

28:18.840 --> 28:20.800
- [Munshi] The partnership is working.
- [chuckles]

28:21.320 --> 28:22.640
May it succeed.

28:22.720 --> 28:23.720
[chuckles]

28:23.800 --> 28:26.280
Mr Munshi, I took off the board.

28:26.800 --> 28:29.000
But what will the chamber's new name be?

28:30.280 --> 28:32.440
Well, the partners of the chamber
will decide that.

28:32.520 --> 28:34.360
What's there to decide?

28:34.440 --> 28:35.840
Balli, Negi and Associates.

28:35.920 --> 28:37.440
- Let's shake on it.
- [Sujata, Munshi laugh]

28:37.520 --> 28:39.040
Sounds good,

28:39.120 --> 28:41.840
but, uh, Negi, Balli and Associates
is also good.

28:41.920 --> 28:42.960
It's witty, right?

28:43.040 --> 28:44.160
Let's shake on it.

28:44.960 --> 28:48.960
Uh, it is a good idea…
[stammering] …but the thing is,

28:49.040 --> 28:51.480
since everyone knows
the bar president's name,

28:51.560 --> 28:54.360
so let's go with
Balli, Negi and Associates.

28:54.440 --> 28:57.040
Uh, listen, Order. Go get a box
of sweets quickly, good boy.

28:57.120 --> 28:58.320
- Sure.
- Hang on, Order.

28:58.400 --> 29:01.080
You're still acting bar president, Mintu.

29:01.160 --> 29:03.160
What if you lose the election by mistake?

29:03.240 --> 29:05.600
Negi, Balli and Associates would be safer.

29:06.560 --> 29:08.560
Order. Now, get the sweets.

29:08.640 --> 29:09.680
No, hang on.

29:10.760 --> 29:13.240
I lose? I lose the election?

29:13.320 --> 29:15.480
Is… You mean, this is
what you want for your new partner?

29:16.000 --> 29:18.160
You just showed me
what a petty foyer lawyer you are.

29:18.240 --> 29:20.520
- [stammers] Hey, one minute.
- Oh, I'm the one who's petty?

29:20.600 --> 29:22.600
Who knocked down my files
twice this morning?

29:22.680 --> 29:25.160
Mr Munshi, this man's a total file maniac.

29:25.240 --> 29:28.760
Really? And what about that little
hand-to-hand contact you just pulled?

29:28.840 --> 29:30.160
"Thank you, Mintu."

29:30.240 --> 29:32.720
- You were there. Tell him what happened.
- How can you talk like that?

29:32.800 --> 29:34.640
- Don't you know how to talk to a woman?
- Maybe I don't.

29:34.720 --> 29:35.720
[Munshi] Enough.

29:36.880 --> 29:40.560
This chamber has always had
the most capable lawyers in Patparganj.

29:42.040 --> 29:44.640
And every decision
will be based on capability.

29:50.640 --> 29:55.040
The chamber's cases and associates
will be divided between you two.

29:55.840 --> 29:57.720
And in the next quarter,

29:57.800 --> 30:02.640
whoever provides relief to more clients
will get to name the chamber.

30:02.720 --> 30:05.480
Oh, I see. So we are making teams, is it?

30:05.560 --> 30:08.240
Madam. Pull on finger, please.

30:08.000 --> 30:18.000
ভুয়া লিংক এড়িয়ে চলুন — অফিসিয়াল: -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

30:08.320 --> 30:09.680
[chuckles] Sorry.

30:11.760 --> 30:13.680
- Hey. Out!
- Buzz off.

30:14.320 --> 30:15.320
Get lost.

30:17.320 --> 30:21.000
The name of the chamber
will be Balli, Negi and Associates.

30:21.080 --> 30:22.880
- That's--
- Which means Ba-Ne.

30:24.080 --> 30:27.440
Negi, Balli and Associates.

30:27.520 --> 30:28.840
Ne-Ba.

30:28.920 --> 30:31.240
- [Mintu laughing]
- [laughing]

30:32.040 --> 30:33.040
SUJATA - MINTU

30:33.120 --> 30:34.520
- [Mintu] Sounds like "never."
- [laughing]

30:50.360 --> 30:51.440
Tea?

30:53.920 --> 30:55.720
[Tyagi] Were you, too,
a lawyer before this?

30:57.000 --> 31:00.440
[chuckles] Why? What did you think?
I was a tea seller?

31:00.520 --> 31:01.560
No, uh…

31:02.560 --> 31:06.600
Do… Do you feel any different,
uh, after taking your oath?

31:06.680 --> 31:10.520
Remember, I stumbled in front of you
under the weight of duty.

31:10.600 --> 31:12.640
Is the weight of duty too much? Or…

31:13.640 --> 31:14.960
are we just used to stumbling?

31:15.040 --> 31:19.200
[chuckles] Beyond reasonable doubt,
it's hard to say, Mr Tyagi.

31:19.280 --> 31:20.960
- Some tea for you.
- Ah, thank you.

31:21.040 --> 31:22.040
[sighs]

31:23.360 --> 31:25.320
You carry the whole tea stall with you.

31:25.400 --> 31:27.680
[chuckling] It's a passion.

31:29.440 --> 31:30.440
Oh.

31:31.000 --> 31:32.800
Someone once told me that, uh,

31:34.000 --> 31:37.800
after taking the oath,
a man changes somewhat.

31:42.560 --> 31:43.720
I took the oath…

31:45.320 --> 31:46.400
correctly, didn't I?

31:50.400 --> 31:51.440
Mr Tyagi.

31:53.800 --> 31:55.280
It's about your beliefs.

31:55.960 --> 31:56.960
Like, uh…

31:58.400 --> 31:59.520
swearing on something.

32:00.320 --> 32:03.680
Some people swear by their mother
and never tell any lies.

32:03.760 --> 32:06.480
[chuckling] And some even
swear by their dead mothers.

32:06.560 --> 32:08.200
- Right?
- [chuckles]

32:08.280 --> 32:09.760
So what it comes down to is,

32:10.360 --> 32:15.040
if you think this oath
is going to help you become a judge,

32:16.240 --> 32:17.280
then take it again.

32:18.600 --> 32:21.280
[tender music playing]

32:22.200 --> 32:24.960
I spent the whole day struggling
with the thought of…

32:26.600 --> 32:30.320
how I would retake my oath
in front of everyone.

32:31.480 --> 32:32.520
Mr Tyagi.

32:33.880 --> 32:37.240
If you're taking this oath for yourself,

32:38.840 --> 32:40.440
why care about the others?

32:48.280 --> 32:50.280
Ani, guess what happened in the chamber.

32:52.160 --> 32:55.080
Why are you drinking plain water?
What happened to her?

32:55.160 --> 32:57.160
She says this is the first time
she's lost to Nayana.

32:57.240 --> 32:58.280
[Nayana] Wrong.

32:58.360 --> 33:00.520
You forgot the spoon race in second grade.

33:00.600 --> 33:01.640
[whispers] Go get her.

33:02.640 --> 33:03.640
Spoon race?

33:04.520 --> 33:07.680
You cheated back then,
and today, you cheated again.

33:08.280 --> 33:10.240
You went crying to your mama back then.

33:10.320 --> 33:11.520
Go cry to her again.

33:11.600 --> 33:13.880
- Well, at least I have a mum.
- [Vishwas gasps]

33:16.360 --> 33:17.360
[whispers] What was that?

33:17.960 --> 33:20.000
[inhales shakily] I'm sorry.

33:20.080 --> 33:21.080
It's okay.

33:24.280 --> 33:25.440
Mr Banaspati.

33:26.480 --> 33:29.080
My settlement offer
still stands at 100 grand.

33:30.160 --> 33:32.480
You've already seen what she's capable of.

33:32.560 --> 33:34.960
I will crush you under my Jimmy Choos.

33:35.040 --> 33:37.240
One minute. One minute.

33:37.320 --> 33:38.880
This case isn't over yet.

33:38.960 --> 33:39.960
Ani, tell her.

33:43.000 --> 33:45.320
Mr Banaspati, you work it out.

33:45.400 --> 33:46.440
- What?
- Huh?

33:47.040 --> 33:48.640
- What?
- Hundred grand.

33:48.720 --> 33:50.320
Seal the deal.

33:51.680 --> 33:53.680
Come on, Mr Banaspati.

33:53.760 --> 33:55.600
Shake on it. Quick.

33:56.520 --> 33:58.160
Come on, Mr Banaspati.

33:59.360 --> 34:00.640
[upbeat music playing]

34:00.720 --> 34:02.480
We are fighting this case.

34:03.920 --> 34:05.520
And not just 100 grand.

34:06.120 --> 34:08.560
I'm going to take 500 grand
as compensation.

34:08.640 --> 34:11.280
- [chuckles]
- [Ani] Thank you, Mr Banaspati.

34:11.360 --> 34:15.280
And I promise you, we will win.

34:15.360 --> 34:18.000
[chuckles] And then
I'll get a Russian wife.

34:18.920 --> 34:21.120
And she will make me
some Russian "salard."

34:21.720 --> 34:23.800
It's "salad." [chuckles]

34:24.400 --> 34:26.400
And that's… that's so sexist.

34:26.480 --> 34:27.560
I know.

34:28.600 --> 34:31.200
You guys are so weird.

34:32.520 --> 34:35.440
- Thank you.
- I, Visheshwar Dayal Tyagi,

34:36.040 --> 34:37.040
having been appointed as

34:37.120 --> 34:39.080
- the Principal District Judge…
- Come. Let's see.

34:39.160 --> 34:40.520
…of Patparganj District Court,

34:40.600 --> 34:42.640
do swear in the name of God

34:42.720 --> 34:48.480
that I will bear true faith and allegiance
to the Constitution of India.

34:48.560 --> 34:53.520
As by law established, that I will uphold
the sovereignty and integrity of India,

34:53.600 --> 34:55.080
that I will duly and faithfully

34:55.160 --> 34:58.720
and to the best of my ability,
knowledge and judgement,

34:58.800 --> 35:00.880
perform the duties of my office

35:00.960 --> 35:06.760
without fear of favour,
affection or ill will.

35:06.840 --> 35:11.280
Finally, Patparganj
has a Principal District Judge.

35:12.080 --> 35:13.080
Agreed?

35:14.720 --> 35:16.400
- Sir?
- Mmm.

35:17.440 --> 35:19.440
Sir, even when you agree, you're angry.

35:19.520 --> 35:21.160
- [chuckles]
- [scoffs]

35:21.240 --> 35:24.120
So far, he's only completed step one,
Mr Shubhkela.

35:25.160 --> 35:28.680
Let's see how true he stays to his oath.

35:28.760 --> 35:30.520
[applauding, cheering]

35:30.600 --> 35:33.400
[triumphant techno music playing]
